1X. HORATIUS COCLES.

Horatius Cocles: note that bis surname, like many oi the ·

Roman cognomino, was derived from a personal peculiarity. The story of Horatius was one of the most celebrated legends ol the early history of Rome, and has been made one of the most familiar to modern readers by Macaulay's Lay of Horatius. There are two versions of the story. According to Livy, whom Macaulay follows, Horatius had two companions; according to Polybius, he defended the bridge alone, but perished in the river. Our version is a combination of the two. ’
